    <h1>Soft 404</h1>
    <p class="description">A page that returns HTTP 200 OK but has no useful content — so Google treats it as not-found anyway. Wastes crawl budget, kills indexing, and at scale signals <strong>poor content quality to the entire domain</strong>.</p>
    <div class="post-meta">
      <div class="meta-author">
        <div class="meta-avatar">AVR</div>
        <div class="meta-author-info">
          <span class="meta-author-name"><a href="/authors/akshay-vr/">Akshay VR</a></span>
